race.comment: Onto our feature of the day, the G3 Coongy Cup and two horses appeal at the early odds. The first of those is QUIETNESS (11) who resumed in a BM88 at Randwick, running on strongly off a good tempo to grab third in an encouraging return. She didn't win last time in but ran some good races over this sort of trip and now into her second Australian campaign, she can elevate second up for the in form yard. Also respecting WOOTTON VERNI (10) for Chris Waller. Three runs back have been solid, good in a strongly run mile two back before grinding home at 1800m last start, beaten 2.9 lengths by Charterhouse and Globe, the latter of whom is now a G1 winner. Gets to 2000m now and sets up nicely. STATUARIO (7) chased home Caulfield Cup favourite Half Yours last start and should be peaking now. Tricky draw but has strong claims. FUTURE HISTORY (1) could be an improver, his best is good enough.
